OL,3,CCouncil leader warns Labour is
OL,4,C'kicking rural England'
OL,6,FDorset, Somerset and Wiltshire
OL,7,FCouncils have already expressed
OL,8,Finterest in working together under the
OL,9,FHeart of Wessex Combined Authority,
OL,10,Fthough they have made clear they don't
OL,11,Fsupport the mayoral model.
OL,13,F"So, at that point, I sat down with
OL,14,Fthe (council) leaders of Somerset and
OL,15,FDorset, and Bournemouth, Christchurch
OL,16,Fand Poole, and we all agreed, yes,
OL,17,Fwe're going to need to put in the bid
OL,18,Fwith that mayor. But we need to make
OL,19,Fsure it's a strong, rural voice,
OL,20,Fbecause at the moment all the mayors
OL,21,Fare urban mayors."
