OL,3,CCouncil leader warns Labour is
OL,4,C'kicking rural England'
OL,6,FDevon and Torbay have already signed a
OL,7,Fdeal which will transfer some powers
OL,8,Fout of Westminster, but the government
OL,9,Fis hoping local authorities will
OL,10,Faccept the highest possible option,
OL,11,Fand sign up to combined authorities.
OL,13,FPerran Moon, Labour MP for Camborne
OL,14,Fand Redruth, denied the claim that
OL,15,Fareas like Cornwall will be forced to
OL,16,Faccept a mayor, after a level three
OL,17,Fdevolution deal was abandoned by the
OL,18,Fcouncil last year.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
