OL,3,CCouncil leader warns Labour is
OL,4,C'kicking rural England'
OL,6,FSpeaking on 12 December, he said: "We
OL,7,Fwon't be forced to have (an elected
OL,8,Fmayor), absolutely not. There'll be no
OL,9,Fpart of England that will be forced to
OL,10,Fhave a mayor."
OL,12,FIt comes after Angela Rayner, the
OL,13,FDeputy Prime Minister, told ITV West
OL,14,FCountry that she is "enticing" Cornish
OL,15,Fvoters to embrace having an elected
OL,16,Fmayor last week.
OL,26,@oD@YpmpD@Fpn
